East London police are searching for two men accused of robbing a travel agency businessman of R60000 at gunpoint in the foyer of the East London Road Lodge Hotel. The robbery last Wednesday took place in front of three staff members and a manager of the Road Lodge.The complainant in the case, Thompson Muyiwa, said the police investigation was being hindered because the hotel did not have CCTV cameras.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.